President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued a proclamation declaring June 14, 2021, as Flag Day and the week starting June 13, 2021, as National Flag Week in the United States. He urges all Americans to display the flag during this week and encourages them to honor the American spirit, celebrate history, and uphold foundational values. The proclamation emphasizes the significance of the American flag as a symbol of unity, liberty, and democracy. It highlights how the flag has been present in historical events, such as being flown on battlefields and journeying to the Moon and Mars. The proclamation also mentions the importance of the flag in communicating the promise of freedom, justice, and equality for all. The President directs federal government buildings to display the flag and encourages citizens to publicly recite the Pledge of Allegiance.